        • [ - ] nobias - member since 12-Dec-15

          @FootballFanatic The significance of goal scorers and assist providers is often inflated. Sometimes forwards are just involved in the final touch of a team move, yet under the influence of mass media people will give all credits to the scorers and neglect other's effort. Same goes to assist provider, media and people praise them for giving an assist when all they did was just giving a square pass to players nearby, such as Messi's assist in this match. Therefore more aspects such as space creation, facilitation of team play and chances creation should also be taken into account when assessing an attacking player's influence in one match. Messi's influence in this match can be seen through his space and chance creation, dribbling and tons of through balls. He is totally justified for getting a high rating. However it is a stone fact that he missed a chance and whoscored didn't take it into account. Maybe the site can add an aspect of chances missed in future games.
